result.execSummary:
The defendant Duane J. Baumgartner was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Deliver Schedule I, II Narcotics, a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(a).
  • Deliver Schedule I, II Narcotics, a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(a).
  • Deliver Schedule I, II Narcotics, a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

miscConds.notes: Court orders bond & attorney fee's in the amount of $1550.00 to be applied to Attorney fees first. Balance of costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. Court directs defendant to obtain any prescription from ONE doctor and fill the prescription at ONE pharmacy. Court requires supervising agent to be provided with prescriptions and amounts prescriptions are to be taken in.
Defendant is to comply with any rules/recommendations as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.  DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.

records.addlTxt: 11:14 am case called. Defendant Duane J. Baumgartner in court with attorney Jeffrey Allen Mann.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Agreement stated on record. Attorney Mann concurs. Preliminary hearing waived. Court questions defendant regarding waiver and accepts waiver. Court has read the complaint, finds probable cause and enters an order binding the defendant over for trial. Information filed. Attorney Mann confirms receipt, waives formal reading-entry of pleas.   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: No Contest to Counts 3, 4, & 5-without second and subsequent enhancer.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismisses and reads-in Counts 1 & 2. Sentencing argument by DA Blader. Sentencing argument by Attorney Mann-defendant waives PSI-court accepts waiver. Statement by defendant. Statement by Court. Court sentences the defendant to: SWD and places on probation for a period of 3 years. CONDITIONS on COUNT 3 ONLY- 5 months WCJ, with Huber and No Good Time Credit. Credit for 17 days served. To begin no later than April 1, 2016. Does not object to jail transfer. CONDITIONS ON ALL COUNTS:  The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. AODA and follow through, Defendant is to obtain Rx from one single doctor and fill the Rx at one single Pharmacy. Court requires PO to be provided with the Rx and amounts Rx to be taken in.  $1,025.00 Drug Buy Money, Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan to include Attorney Mann's fees to be paid first. Bond to be applied. Terms of Agent. DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice. Appeal Rights Given.
DE's Petition for Adjournment - Granted by the Court

Counsel suggests adjournment to mid-December as negotiations continue.  P/S requested and scheduled.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for December 22, 2015 at 10:45 am.

Case Called @ 1:26 PM: Defendant Duane J. Baumgartner in court, appearing via video, without counsel.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel.   Def wishes to have counsel and requests Court Appt Counsel.  Def not eligible for SPD due to assets owned.  Employed part time.  Upon discussion of earnings, Court will appoint counsel with a deposit paid by 7/10/2015 of $250.00 with a PP commencing on 8/1/2015 an add'l $100 per month payment.  ADA argues for Cash Bond of $1000.00 w/conditions.  Def makes statement as to bond, requests Signature Bond be implemented.  Def will not be able to post cash bond as requested.  The Court:  Orders Cash Bond of $1000.00 with conditions as requested.  IA Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State and probable cause finding as to each count alleged within the complaint.  Initial appearance scheduled for July 28, 2015 at 02:45 pm.
